search::addSearchType()

Description
    Sets class array variable, $this->searchTypes[], to the value of $attPairs.
    public null search::addSearchType(string $attPairs)

Parameters
    attPairs
	An array containing name/value pairs.

Examples
    <?php
	...
	$searchObj = new search($engine);
	$searchObj->relevanceSearch = TRUE;
	$type = array();
	$type['name']  = "keyword";
	$type['label'] = "Keyword";
	$searchObj->addSearchType($type);
	unset($type);
	...
    ?>

See Also
    search::addToSearchType()

